The requirements for an EB-1C (Multinational Manager or Executive) petition for a foreign national include the following:

The petitioning company must be a U.S. employer;
The foreign national must be a manager or executive of the petitioning company;
The petitioning company must have a qualifying relationship with a foreign company;
The foreign national must have been employed abroad in a managerial or executive capacity by the foreign company for one continuous year within the three years immediately preceding the filing of the petition; and
The foreign national must be seeking to enter the U.S. to continue to work for the same employer or one affiliated with the petitioning company.

A petitioning company may also qualify as an "acceptable entity" if it is a foreign company that:
Has been doing business for one continuous year as an affiliate, subsidiary, or branch of the petitioning U.S. employer in the U.S. for the one-year period preceding the petition filing; and
During this one-year period, was doing business as an affiliate, subsidiary, or branch of the petitioning U.S. employer in the U.S.
